\[AB^2\cdot DC + AC^2\cdot BD = BC(AD^2+BD\cdot DC).\]

Substituting the known values, we have $5^2\cdot\frac{15}{8}+3^2\cdot\frac{35}{8}=7(AD^2+\frac{35}{8}\cdot\frac{15}{8})$. This simplifies to $AD^2=\frac{25}{4}$.

